 Nigerian Postal Service PHOTO:NAN  The Federal Capital Territory Fire Service personnel were, however, on hand to contain the fire, which attracted a large crowd at the busy Area 10, Garki, in Abuja. Efforts by a NAN correspondent to get information from officials of the service, on what led to the incident, were abortive. A security officer, who pleaded anonymity, told NAN that the fire started at about 8:40 a.m. An eyewitness, Mr Adamu Bala, said he drew the attention of the security officers guarding the building when he saw smoke coming from the back of the building. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .